    "country_code": "USA",
    "description": "Have you ever ordered a product on Amazon and when that box with the smile arrived, wondered how it got to you so fast? Wondered where it came from and how much it cost Amazon? If so, the Amazon Global Supply Chain Optimization Technology (SCOT) organization is for you.<br/><br/>Watch this video to learn more about our organization, SCOT: http://bit.ly/amazon-scot<br/><br/>We are the Optimal Sourcing Systems team (OSS) within SCOT and are looking for a Data Engineer to join us! OSS designs and builds systems that measure and manage Amazon\u2019s supplier capabilities, identify and react to supply disruptions, and prioritizes inbound freight for our global network. OSS software is used by every country Amazon services, and is a critical link to ensuring Amazon offers the products our customers want, at the lowest possible cost. If you want to work on data that directly impacts how millions of products move through Amazon's global supply chain and you're excited about defining the future of AI-powered data engineering, we'd love to hear from you.<br/><br/>Key job responsibilities<br/>- Build and optimize data pipelines that process large-scale supply chain datasets, enabling real-time visibility into inventory movement and vendor performance<br/>- Design and maintain scalable data warehousing solutions that serve as the foundation for business-critical reporting and analytics<br/>- Harness the power of Generative AI to accelerate data source discovery, streamline pipeline development, and build intelligent agents that help Business Intelligence Engineers and Scientists uncover emerging opportunities<br/>- Create self-service data capabilities and AI-integrated platforms that empower stakeholders to answer key business questions independently<br/>- Partner closely with business and technical stakeholders to understand requirements and translate them into robust, well-architected data solutions<br/><br/>A day in the life<br/>Amazon offers a full range of benefits that support you and eligible family members, including domestic partners and their children. Benefits can vary by location, the number of regularly scheduled hours you work, length of employment, and job status such as seasonal or temporary employment. <br/><br/>The benefits that generally apply to regular, full-time employees include: <br/>- Medical, Dental, and Vision Coverage <br/>- Maternity and Parental Leave Options <br/>- Paid Time Off (PTO) <br/>- 401(k) Plan \u00a0 <br/><br/>If you are not sure that every qualification on the list above describes you exactly, we'd still love to hear from you! <br/><br/>At Amazon, we value people with unique backgrounds, experiences, and skillsets. If you\u2019re passionate about this role and want to make an impact on a global scale, please apply!",
